        <div class="tip">
            <h3>CRITICAL EXAM-DAY TIPS:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>✓ Lindemann 10% rule:</strong> ALWAYS arises in pyramid Qs. Energy at T<sub>n+1</sub> = 10% of T<sub>n</sub>.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Pyramid types:</strong> Energy upright always; Numbers/Biomass can flip in tree/aquatic. Don't confuse.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Hotspot count:</strong> India has 4 (not 3) — Sundaland is the often-missed one (Nicobar).</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Hotspot criteria:</strong> 1500 endemic plants + 70% loss of primary vegetation. Both required.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Biosphere Reserves vs UNESCO listed:</strong> India 18 declared; only 12 are in UNESCO World Network.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Forest cover state ranking:</strong> MP (highest area); Mizoram (highest %). Don't confuse.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Ramsar largest in India:</strong> Sundarbans (not the largest in the world — that's Bolivia's Llanos de Moxos).</li>
                <li><strong>✓ N-fixer mnemonic:</strong> "RAFA-AN" — Rhizobium, Azotobacter, Frankia, Azolla-Anabaena, Nostoc.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Nitrification:</strong> 2-step (Nitrosomonas → Nitrobacter); aerobic; needs SRT &gt; 10 d in WWTP.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Phosphorus has NO gaseous phase</strong> — common Q.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ India NDC: write 45 / 50 / 2.5–3 / 2070</strong> — these are the four canonical numbers.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Per capita water declining:</strong> 5177 → 1486 → projected &lt; 1000 by 2050.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ SDGs adopted 25 Sept 2015;</strong> 17 goals / 169 targets / 232 indicators. Agenda 2030.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Marking strategy:</strong> Unit 8 = 5–7 Qs; mostly factual recall (numbers, species, dates) — high yield per hour of revision.</li>
                <li><strong>✓ Trap:</strong> Lindemann 10% law year = 1942 (not 1927 — that's Elton's pyramid).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

